Class CarmenFeature

  • java.lang.Object
    • Feature
      • com.mapbox.services.api.geocoding.v5.models.CarmenFeature

  • public class CarmenFeature
extends Feature
    The Features key in the geocoding API response contains the majority of information you'll want to use.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    Carmen Geojson information, Mapbox geocoder documentation, Official GeoJSON Feature Specifications

      • getAddress

        public String getAddress()
        A string of the house number for the returned address feature. Note that unlike the address property for poi features, this property is outside the properties object.
        Returns:
        Where applicable. While the string content isn't guaranteed, in many cases, this will be the house number. If the response doesn't contain an address this will be null.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • getContext

        public List<CarmenContext> getContext()
        An array representing the hierarchy of encompassing parent features. Each parent feature may include address, category, tel, maki, landmark, wikidata, or short code.

        Array representing a hierarchy of parents. Each parent includes id, text keys.

      • getMatchingPlaceName

        public String getMatchingPlaceName()
        A string analogous to the getPlaceName() field that more closely matches the query than results in the specified language. For example, querying "Köln, Germany" with language set to English might return a feature with the placeName "Cologne, Germany" and a matching_place_name of "Köln, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany".
        Returns:
        a string containing the matching place name
        Since:
        2.2.0

      • setMatchingPlaceName

        public void setMatchingPlaceName(String matchingPlaceName)
        Set a string analogous to the getPlaceName() field that more closely matches the query than results in the specified language.
        Parameters:
        matchingPlaceName - a string containing the matching place name
        Since:
        2.2.0

      • getMatchingText

        public String getMatchingText()
        A string analogous to the text field that more closely matches the query than results in the specified language. For example, querying "Köln, Germany" with language set to English might return a feature with the text "Cologne" and the matching_text "Köln".
        Returns:
        a string containing the matching text
        Since:
        2.2.0

      • getPlaceType

        public String[] getPlaceType()
        An array of feature types describing the feature. Options are country, region, postcode, district, place, locality, neighborhood, address, poi, and poi.landmark. Most features have only one type, but if the feature has multiple types, (for example, Vatican City is a country, region, and place), all applicable types will be listed in the array.
        Returns:
        a String array containing the place types
        Since:
        2.2.0
